# KMP UTXO — Project Overview

Compose Multiplatform (Kotlin) cryptocurrency app targeting Android, iOS, Desktop, and Web.

## Tech stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| UI | Compose Multiplatform, Material 3 |
| Navigation | Jetpack Navigation Compose (type-safe routes) |
| Networking | Ktor (HTTP + WebSocket) |
| Serialization | kotlinx.serialization |
| Image loading | Coil 3 |
| State persistence | KStore |
| Logging | Kermit (AppLogger) |
| ViewModel | AndroidX Lifecycle ViewModel |

## Features

- **Market screen** — real-time crypto prices via Binance `!miniTicker@arr` WebSocket stream
- **Coin detail** — per-symbol ticker, order book heatmap, kline charts
- **Favorites** — user-curated watchlist persisted with KStore
- **Settings** — theme selection, trading pair preference
- **News feed** — RSS-based crypto news

## Source layout

```
composeApp/src/commonMain/kotlin/
  App.kt                  # Root composable, NavHost, expect declarations
  model/                  # @Serializable data classes
  network/                # Ktor HTTP client, WebSocket services
  ui/                     # Screens, ViewModels, composable components
    utils/                # Chart helpers, shimmer, debounce
    components/           # Reusable UI components (scrollbar, etc.)
  theme/                  # Color tokens, Typography, UTXOTheme
  ktx/                    # Extension functions (formatting, icons)
  logging/                # AppLogger, ServerLogWriter
```

## Build commands

- Build: `./gradlew build`
- Test: `./gradlew test`
- Lint: `./gradlew ktlintCheck`
- Android install: `./gradlew :composeApp:installDebug`
- Desktop run: `./gradlew :composeApp:run`

## Key conventions

- Use `viewModelScope.launch(Dispatchers.Default)` for background work, `withContext(Dispatchers.Main)` for state updates.
- Expose UI state as `StateFlow` with backing `MutableStateFlow`.
- Use `derivedStateOf` and `remember` to minimize recompositions.
- All network models use `@Serializable` with nullable defaults for optional fields.
- Never hardcode colors — use Material theme tokens from `theme/`.
- Use string resources (`Res.string.*`) instead of hardcoded strings.
